{"word":"φιλαίτιος","slug":"φιλαίτιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φιλαίτιος</b></el> <el>(φῐλ-αίτιος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αἰτία'><el>αἰτία</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>fond of accusing, censorious</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:— <el>τὸ φ.</el> <i>censoriousness</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>liable to blame</i> or <i>attack</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}